<item>
            <title>[SPR-1233] AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests onTearDownInTransaction doesn&apos;t throws Exception</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1233</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;tearDown() method in JUnit declares that it throws any Exception, but onTearDownInTransaction() and onTearDownAfterTransaction() doesn&apos;t declare this, so all checked exeptions must be caught.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I want to close a DB connection used for DbUnit, which was created in onSetUpBeforeTransaction() and I have to catch SQLException which looks to me as non conventional.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(In fact due to the rollback capability of this test class I can close the connection immediately after pre-filling the DB so will not need this, but just to point out &quot;the little bug&quot;.)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
