                            <comment id="14372" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2005 05:48:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed - code should be allowed to throw any Exception there. I&apos;ve added this for 1.2.4, even if it might break classes that call &quot;super.onTearDownInTransaction()&quot; in their &quot;onTearDownInTransaction&quot;. They shouldn&apos;t do this anyway, as the parent method is an empty placeholder, but rather just put their plain shutdown code there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
